HEADWORD: Johnnycake
<hw>John"ny*cake`</hw> <pr>(-k⟦amac⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind
of bread made of the meal of maize (Indian corn), mixed with water or
milk, etc., and baked.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>J.
Barlow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
